com.serena.dmclient.objects
Interface BaselineReplicationConfiguration

All Superinterfaces:
DimensionsObject, ReplicationConfiguration
public interface BaselineReplicationConfiguration
extends ReplicationConfiguration

Represents a Dimensions baseline replication configuration. Baseline configurations are used to control the replication of baselines from one base database to another, and replicate items at the baseline level.

Baseline replication is controlled through the use of a baseline configuration definition that allows you to specify a number of additional filters when deciding what items within a baseline will be replicated. Baseline replication replicates the items contained in a baseline to a subordinate site, and then creates a baseline using those replicated items. Only items that match the replication policy are replicated (see below). A single baseline configuration definition can be used to control the replication of many different baselines to one or more subordinate(s).
